# Mixing Algorithms Performance Benchmark Report

**Methodology:**
To evaluate the 5 algorithmic mixing strategies (RMA, BS, AP-DP, LARP, ILP), we ran `100` simulated tests utilizing deeply randomized target fluid ratios. The target accuracy depth `d` was fixed at `8`, processing a dynamic range of `2` to `15` distinct fluid variables simultaneously. The generated data details key operational efficiency parameters such as total mix nodes, tree depth, parallelization requirements, and liquid split boundaries.

## 📊 Average Benchmark Data (100 Iterations)

| Metric | RMA | BS | AP-DP v3 | LARP v2 | ILP v2 |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **m (Mixes)** | 27.59 | 22.50 | 28.02 | 25.57 | 24.97 |
| **d (Tree Depth)** | 7.97 | 7.97 | 7.97 | 7.89 | 7.97 |
| **p (Parallelism)** | 5.17 | 4.29 | 5.25 | 4.76 | 4.66 |
| **Leaves** | 28.59 | 23.50 | 29.02 | 26.57 | 25.97 |
| **Splits** | 20.19 | 15.08 | 20.60 | 18.29 | 17.55 |
| **l (Dilution Sum)** | 20.69 | 10.99 | 20.31 | 18.69 | 17.22 |
| **maxL (Max Dilution)** | 5.75 | 1.73 | 5.69 | 5.72 | 5.49 |

